WEBVTT

00:15.015 --> 00:16.934
(CLATTERING)

00:17.017 --> 00:19.019
ALLY: (WHISPERS) Ivy, did you hear that?

00:19.937 --> 00:21.146
Ivy?

00:22.731 --> 00:23.815
(SCREAMING)

00:29.363 --> 00:32.115
-(TRUMP SPEAKING ON TV)
-There is a clown

00:32.199 --> 00:33.367
in the bed with me!

00:33.450 --> 00:35.077
No! We are calling the police!

00:35.160 --> 00:37.329
Oz is upstairs!

00:38.705 --> 00:40.290
Ivy...

00:40.374 --> 00:42.376
(PANTING)

00:43.377 --> 00:45.003
-Ivy.
-Stay behind me.

00:52.427 --> 00:54.596
(WHISPERING) Where is it?

00:56.598 --> 00:58.058
Okay.

00:58.141 --> 00:59.268
No.

00:59.351 --> 01:01.186
(BOTH PANTING)

01:08.694 --> 01:10.404
(PANTING)

01:14.575 --> 01:16.243
(BOTH PANTING)

01:16.326 --> 01:17.536
Okay.

01:17.619 --> 01:19.079
Where is he?

01:19.162 --> 01:21.373
-He was right there.
-Okay.

01:32.634 --> 01:33.969
There.

01:34.052 --> 01:36.889
He could be in there. In there.

01:40.642 --> 01:42.769
(BREATH TREMBLING)

01:54.698 --> 01:56.617
Is that...

01:56.700 --> 01:59.161
This can't... can't...

02:00.996 --> 02:03.332
This can't be my imagination.

02:06.502 --> 02:07.878
(PANTS) I'm sorry.

02:09.129 --> 02:10.672
(INHALES DEEPLY)

02:10.756 --> 02:14.092
I don't know how much more
of this I can take.

02:26.271 --> 02:28.982
Come here. Come here.

02:33.111 --> 02:34.488
(SIGHS)

02:35.155 --> 02:38.909
I think there might be
something wrong with me.

02:41.870 --> 02:44.998
(CRYING) I don't know what's real anymore.

02:45.082 --> 02:46.542
(SOBS)

02:47.960 --> 02:50.087
I am.

02:50.170 --> 02:51.713
(SNIFFLING)

02:53.131 --> 02:54.800
You are.

02:58.053 --> 03:00.556
What we have together...

03:00.639 --> 03:03.225
(PANTING)

03:03.308 --> 03:05.269
...this is real.

03:41.555 --> 03:43.015
Hmm?

04:06.413 --> 04:07.956
(GASPS SOFTLY)

04:11.668 --> 04:13.712
Scream

04:13.795 --> 04:16.173
and I'll kill you.

04:16.256 --> 04:18.091
(RASPY BREATHING)

04:24.139 --> 04:25.224
(SCREAMS)

04:27.643 --> 04:29.645
(CLOWN YELLING)

04:47.579 --> 04:49.122
(DOORKNOB RATTLES)

05:08.183 --> 05:09.643
OZ: Mom!

05:10.561 --> 05:12.980
(OZ SCREAMING, CRYING)

05:15.649 --> 05:17.776
Oz, Oz.

05:17.860 --> 05:19.444
Wake up, honey.
You're having a night terror.

05:19.528 --> 05:20.529
(GROANING)

05:20.612 --> 05:22.447
-Oz, wake up.
-(PANTING RAPIDLY)

05:22.531 --> 05:23.532
Okay, hon.

05:23.615 --> 05:25.909
Yeah, okay. It's okay.

05:25.993 --> 05:27.828
You're safe now, sweetheart.

05:29.705 --> 05:32.165
The clowns are gonna kill me.

05:33.208 --> 05:35.043
-Come here.
-I want Mom.

05:36.086 --> 05:37.921
-Mom.
-Okay.

05:38.005 --> 05:39.673
Okay.

05:39.756 --> 05:41.633
Yeah.

05:41.717 --> 05:44.052
I'm here, okay?

05:46.054 --> 05:48.307
(THEME MUSIC PLAYING)

06:55.999 --> 06:58.377
NEWSWOMAN: <i>A brutal attack</i>
<i>caught on cell phone video.</i>

06:58.460 --> 07:01.880
<i>What started</i>
<i>as a grotesque example of crime</i>

07:01.964 --> 07:04.216
<i>in a small Michigan town</i>
<i>has taken an unexpected</i>

07:04.299 --> 07:05.968
<i>and political turn.</i>

07:06.051 --> 07:09.388
<i>It was a week ago today</i>
<i>that local man Kai Anderson</i>

07:09.471 --> 07:13.642
<i>was badly beaten by migrant workers</i>
<i>outside of a local hardware store.</i>

07:13.725 --> 07:16.520
<i>The attack was filmed</i>
<i>by Meadow and Harrison Wilton</i>

07:16.603 --> 07:19.481
<i>and given exclusively to us</i>
<i>here at Channel 7.</i>

07:19.565 --> 07:22.025
HARRISON: <i>The video doesn't even convey</i>
<i>how awful it was.</i>

07:22.109 --> 07:24.403
Oh, thank goodness for modern technology.

07:24.486 --> 07:26.488
I just hope it helps them
convict those guys.

07:26.572 --> 07:28.365
NEWSWOMAN: <i>The attackers are being held</i>

07:28.448 --> 07:31.326
<i>in an ICE detention facility,</i>
<i>while authorities decide</i>

07:31.410 --> 07:34.997
<i>whether to make them stand trial</i>
<i>or to deport them immediately.</i>

07:35.080 --> 07:38.166
I'm disgusted and outraged.

07:39.626 --> 07:42.379
When President Trump called them
criminals and rapists,

07:42.462 --> 07:45.549
he was viciously attacked
by the PC police.

07:45.632 --> 07:47.593
(ON TV) <i>I grew up in this town,</i>

07:47.676 --> 07:49.636
<i>and I remember</i>
<i>when our communities were safe,</i>

07:49.720 --> 07:51.513
<i>but they're not anymore.</i>

07:51.597 --> 07:53.140
<i>Look at my face.</i>

07:54.683 --> 07:56.810
<i>Look at my face, Michigan!</i>

07:56.894 --> 07:58.187
I'm done complaining.

07:58.270 --> 08:00.272
Which is why I'm here at City Hall

08:00.355 --> 08:02.316
picking up my paperwork
so I can officially run

08:02.399 --> 08:06.028
for the seat on the city council
that was made vacant...

08:06.111 --> 08:07.487
(EXHALES)

08:07.571 --> 08:10.657
...by the tragic murder
of Councilman Chang.

08:10.741 --> 08:12.201
(SIGHS)

08:12.284 --> 08:14.912
<i>-Just vote Kai Anderson.</i>
-(VEHICLE APPROACHING)

08:14.995 --> 08:17.456
<i>Vote for the man</i>
<i>who can take your fear away.</i>

08:17.539 --> 08:19.291
<i>They're out there.</i>

08:19.374 --> 08:21.627
NEWSWOMAN:
<i>More on the campaign</i> as it progresses.

08:21.710 --> 08:23.837
<i>Beverly Hope, Channel 7 News.</i>

08:23.921 --> 08:25.756
<i>Bob, back to you.</i>

09:00.207 --> 09:01.959
(ENGINE STARTS)

09:39.288 --> 09:41.290
(BIRDS CHIRPING)

09:57.264 --> 09:59.266
-HARRISON: Can I help you?
-Uh...

10:19.870 --> 10:22.206
Ladies and gentlemen,
tonight we need to hum

10:22.289 --> 10:25.501
like a well-oiled machine,
as Ivy is leaving early.

10:25.584 --> 10:26.960
That means all stations cleaned,

10:27.044 --> 10:30.214
all food prepped a half hour
before we open.

10:30.297 --> 10:31.924
When Ivy is gone I am in charge.

10:32.007 --> 10:34.801
That means when I talk, you listen. Pedro.

10:34.885 --> 10:37.554
It also means we will speak English only
in my kitchen,

10:37.638 --> 10:39.014
so we can all communicate.

10:39.097 --> 10:40.307
<i>(SWEARS IN SPANISH)</i>

10:40.390 --> 10:43.477
Fuck you! You get that cholo shit
out of my kitchen

10:43.560 --> 10:45.562
before I shove this ladle up your ass.

10:45.646 --> 10:46.939
-Bring it, <i>pendejo.</i>
-English, goddamn...

10:47.022 --> 10:49.149
Hey! Whoa, whoa, whoa,
what the hell, you two?

10:49.233 --> 10:51.235
Put it down, both of you. Now.

10:52.903 --> 10:54.905
Get back to work, Pedro.

10:57.157 --> 10:59.284
-(WHISPERS) You need to fire this asshole.
-I'm not about to fire

10:59.368 --> 11:01.537
an immigrant in this climate.

11:04.122 --> 11:05.290
Where's Ivy?

11:11.046 --> 11:12.506
You're lucky, bitch.

11:15.425 --> 11:17.427
(RUNNING FOOTFALLS)

11:21.098 --> 11:23.517
Oz? Oz.

11:33.569 --> 11:35.904
So, what, you're not talking to me today?

11:35.988 --> 11:37.698
I got homework.

11:37.781 --> 11:39.783
Liar. You've been
throwing shade ever since

11:39.867 --> 11:41.869
I picked you up from school.

11:44.413 --> 11:46.623
Here. I got this for you.

11:46.707 --> 11:48.166
Just don't tell your moms.

11:48.250 --> 11:49.376
Look, Oz.

11:49.459 --> 11:52.212
What did you tell my moms
about what happened across the street?

11:52.296 --> 11:53.755
They think I made everything up.

11:53.839 --> 11:56.049
No, they think you imagined it.

11:56.133 --> 11:57.301
It's a little bit different.

11:57.384 --> 12:00.512
-Are you making fun of me?
-Look, Oz,

12:00.596 --> 12:03.640
people are going to believe
what they're going to believe.

12:03.724 --> 12:06.101
The trick is figuring out
what they want to believe

12:06.185 --> 12:08.187
and then giving it to them.

12:13.609 --> 12:15.360
What are you doing?

12:15.444 --> 12:16.695
You're scared.

12:20.824 --> 12:21.825
(DISTORTED SCREAMS)

12:21.909 --> 12:23.827
What if they come back?

12:24.953 --> 12:27.372
The ones who really did it.

12:27.456 --> 12:29.833
They won't come back for you.

12:29.917 --> 12:32.920
How do you know? I was a witness.

12:33.003 --> 12:35.005
But nobody knows that. Right?

12:38.550 --> 12:40.469
Give me your pinky.

12:40.552 --> 12:42.513
Why?

12:42.596 --> 12:45.807
I'm going to show you a trick.
It's going to help you.

12:45.891 --> 12:47.184
Come on.

12:48.185 --> 12:49.561
Pinky to pinky.

12:54.107 --> 12:55.817
We're connected, Oz.

12:55.901 --> 12:58.445
Flesh to flesh.

12:58.529 --> 13:00.405
If you lie, I'll know.

13:01.698 --> 13:03.617
You're afraid of the house
across the street.

13:03.700 --> 13:06.245
You wouldn't even look at it
when we got home.

13:06.328 --> 13:09.289
I wish we'd never gone over there.

13:10.707 --> 13:13.001
Did you notice somebody's moving in?

13:13.085 --> 13:14.878
How did that make you feel?

13:17.297 --> 13:19.383
-Nervous.
-Afraid.

13:19.466 --> 13:22.135
Pinky to pinky.

13:22.219 --> 13:24.721
Flesh to flesh.

13:24.805 --> 13:27.599
You're going to give me your fear, Oz.

13:27.683 --> 13:30.269
I'm going to keep it for you.

13:30.352 --> 13:33.272
It's gonna make us both stronger.

13:37.484 --> 13:39.027
Oz?

13:42.155 --> 13:43.991
Ozymandias?

13:46.201 --> 13:47.661
Ozzie?

13:48.704 --> 13:50.080
(DOOR CLOSES)

13:50.163 --> 13:51.498
WINTER: He's across the street
with the new neighbors.

13:51.582 --> 13:53.625
I just came back to grab a jacket for him.

13:55.169 --> 13:57.129
He's there alone?

13:57.212 --> 13:58.380
Yeah. They're super cool.

13:58.463 --> 14:00.465
Oh, my God.

14:03.510 --> 14:05.554
Oz!

14:05.637 --> 14:06.930
(OZ SQUEALS)

14:07.014 --> 14:08.348
Jesus Christ.

14:08.432 --> 14:09.850
Oz!

14:11.476 --> 14:12.519
-Awesome.
-I know, right?

14:12.603 --> 14:15.147
Ozzie! Ozzie, get away from there!

14:15.230 --> 14:16.231
You could get stung.

14:16.315 --> 14:18.609
We don't know if you're allergic or not.
Come here.

14:18.692 --> 14:20.611
Oh, no, no, no, it's fine.
They don't sting.

14:20.694 --> 14:22.070
Not when they're gainfully employed.

14:22.154 --> 14:23.864
Moms, look at the honeycombs.

14:35.083 --> 14:37.002
MEADOW: Is she okay?

14:37.085 --> 14:38.253
It's too much sun.

14:38.337 --> 14:41.507
No, I'm... I'm fine.

14:41.590 --> 14:42.758
Hey, I'm Harrison.

14:42.841 --> 14:44.968
Harrison Wilton. This is my wife, Meadow.

14:45.052 --> 14:46.512
I... I'm sorry, I hope it's okay that we

14:46.595 --> 14:48.847
invited the kid over to
see our little colony.

14:48.931 --> 14:50.307
Children get such a kick out of it.

14:50.390 --> 14:52.809
-Kind of makes us feel like kids again.
-(LAUGHS)

14:52.893 --> 14:55.604
How do you know they don't sting?

14:55.687 --> 15:00.609
I read about a beekeeper in California
who was killed by his bees.

15:00.692 --> 15:03.904
If there is a story about
something horrible happening,

15:03.987 --> 15:06.031
-Ally knows about it.
-(LAUGHTER)

15:06.114 --> 15:12.412
I'm sorry. I'm Ivy Mayfair-Richards,
and this is my very worried wife, Ally.

15:12.496 --> 15:15.791
Oh, thank God. I always say the best way
to bring up property values

15:15.874 --> 15:18.168
is to have some lesbians move in.

15:18.252 --> 15:19.795
Responsible homeowners.

15:19.878 --> 15:21.255
Usually one of you is handy.

15:21.338 --> 15:23.423
I'm guessing that would be you.

15:24.883 --> 15:27.719
What was up with you earlier,
Little Miss Snoopy-pants?

15:29.721 --> 15:31.139
Uh, sorry, I, um...

15:31.223 --> 15:32.850
(CLEARS THROAT)

15:32.933 --> 15:35.644
I'm sorry. I just...
I was a little unnerved

15:35.727 --> 15:38.146
by someone moving in
so soon after the incident.

15:38.230 --> 15:40.315
Oh, you mean the murder-suicide?

15:40.399 --> 15:41.900
Ooh...

15:41.984 --> 15:43.902
(BOTH LAUGHING)

15:43.986 --> 15:47.739
I'm sorry. It makes us feel better
to have a sense of humor about it.

15:47.823 --> 15:50.409
Truth be told, as soon as we saw
what happened on the news,

15:50.492 --> 15:51.952
we called the owners of the house.

15:53.161 --> 15:54.580
The Changs were renters?

15:55.956 --> 15:57.374
I didn't know that.

15:57.457 --> 16:01.670
We had a feeling the owners
would be motivated to sell.

16:01.753 --> 16:02.880
And they were.

16:02.963 --> 16:04.715
We've had some credit issues.

16:04.798 --> 16:07.342
A foreclosure, followed by the big B-word.

16:07.426 --> 16:09.553
So, uh, it's been hard.

16:09.636 --> 16:12.556
These owners just
signed over the lease to us.

16:12.639 --> 16:17.060
Wow. You guys are so honest.

16:17.144 --> 16:21.648
Oh. (LAUGHS) Well,
it's the way of the world now, right?

16:21.732 --> 16:23.442
Lay it all out there.

16:23.525 --> 16:26.153
You know? Radical, fearless honesty.

16:26.236 --> 16:29.031
Facebook, Twitter, blah, blah, blah.

16:29.114 --> 16:32.075
"Everyone look at me," right?
Excuse me, sir.

16:32.159 --> 16:34.912
To answer your question from before,

16:34.995 --> 16:38.624
a hive is the perfect natural community,

16:38.707 --> 16:40.918
because every single member of the hive

16:41.001 --> 16:43.879
is completely committed 100%
to a singular task.

16:43.962 --> 16:46.673
There's no arguments,
there's no complaints, there's no "me."

16:47.841 --> 16:49.843
I admire them.

16:52.262 --> 16:54.473
Would you guys like
some Crystal Light lemonade?

16:54.556 --> 16:56.767
I need to get out of the sun.

17:05.651 --> 17:09.488
I can't drink this stuff
without thinking of BeyoncÃ© now.

17:09.571 --> 17:11.198
Thank you for coming in.

17:11.281 --> 17:13.575
I have this ongoing battle with the sun.

17:13.659 --> 17:16.078
I used to love it.
I fried myself like bacon.

17:16.161 --> 17:18.997
But then I had skin cancer
a couple years back,

17:19.081 --> 17:21.458
so I never spend
more than 10 minutes outside at a time.

17:21.542 --> 17:23.168
I still get melanomas.

17:23.252 --> 17:24.962
It's global warming.

17:25.045 --> 17:26.880
We're all gonna get cancer.

17:26.964 --> 17:30.217
Had to quit my job.
I was in pharmaceuticals.

17:30.300 --> 17:33.595
I work from home now, and Etsy is my life.

17:33.679 --> 17:37.140
-Big Nicole Kidman fans, huh?
-Oh, the biggest.

17:37.224 --> 17:40.185
We're co-vice presidents
of the Michigan chapter of her fan club.

17:40.269 --> 17:42.729
Have you seen <i>Big Little Lies?</i>
She's transcendent.

17:42.813 --> 17:44.314
Sweetheart,

17:44.398 --> 17:46.650
-your gay is showing.
-Wait, I'm...

17:46.733 --> 17:48.277
You're gay?

17:48.360 --> 17:49.736
Yeah. (CHUCKLES)

17:49.820 --> 17:52.030
We were besties in high school
and we made a pact.

17:52.114 --> 17:54.825
If we weren't married by 35,
we'd marry each other.

17:54.908 --> 17:58.662
He gets one night a week
in Detroit to do whatever.

17:58.745 --> 18:03.041
And the rule is no making a fool of me
and take your Truvada.

18:03.125 --> 18:04.835
And, you know, Meadow doesn't
really like to be touched

18:04.918 --> 18:08.422
because of her cancer, so...

18:08.505 --> 18:10.132
Kind of all works out.

18:13.051 --> 18:17.055
Wow. Uh, you know,
we have just blathered on, haven't we?

18:17.139 --> 18:18.265
Tell us about you.

18:20.601 --> 18:23.061
We need to go, um, actually.

18:23.145 --> 18:25.397
We need to get Oz into the bath.

18:25.480 --> 18:27.149
-Oh.
-But thank you so much

18:27.232 --> 18:28.775
for your hospitality.

18:28.859 --> 18:30.444
Well, drop by anytime,

18:30.527 --> 18:33.071
if you want to hang or watch Bravo
or something.

18:33.155 --> 18:35.032
I watch all the <i>Real Housewives,</i>
even <i>Atlanta.</i>

18:35.115 --> 18:38.827
-Hey, do you go to SoulCycle?
-And, if you ever want a real workout,

18:38.911 --> 18:41.330
I'm a trainer over at
Funtime Fitness in Northville.

18:41.413 --> 18:43.373
Oh, I'm addicted to Pilates.

18:43.457 --> 18:44.708
Doesn't it upset you?

18:46.710 --> 18:50.214
To be here so soon after what happened?

18:50.297 --> 18:52.299
We don't scare easily.

19:03.185 --> 19:05.187
It was nice meeting you.

19:07.564 --> 19:09.149
ALLY: Ozzie?

19:11.485 --> 19:14.947
Yeah, they're eccentric,
but they seem nice enough.

19:15.030 --> 19:17.449
Ivy, come on, the barrels?

19:17.533 --> 19:20.244
What is that about?
What could they possibly be storing

19:20.327 --> 19:22.371
in such mass quantities?

19:22.454 --> 19:25.082
What they do is none of our business.

19:25.165 --> 19:27.084
You aren't at all suspicious?

19:27.167 --> 19:28.710
-No. (LAUGHS)
-Why not? It's so str...

19:28.794 --> 19:30.671
-Moms.
-Hi, honey.

19:30.754 --> 19:32.798
-I can't sleep.
-Sweetheart,

19:32.881 --> 19:35.551
we told you not to eat chocolate
before you go to sleep.

19:35.634 --> 19:37.928
-I didn't.
-Ozzie.

19:38.011 --> 19:41.014
I don't want to sleep in my bedroom.

19:41.098 --> 19:43.308
I'm scared.

19:46.687 --> 19:47.938
Okay.

19:48.021 --> 19:51.650
Come here. There's plenty of room.
It's a California king.

19:53.277 --> 19:54.987
-Come on.
-Get in here.

19:55.070 --> 19:57.322
-Get in here!
-Oh, my goodness,

19:57.406 --> 19:59.408
-there's so much tickling!
-(CELL PHONE VIBRATES)

19:59.491 --> 20:01.994
-And there's chin tickling and there's...
-Shit.

20:02.077 --> 20:03.787
What is it? What's the matter?

20:03.871 --> 20:05.706
Something tripped the security system
at the restaurant.

20:05.789 --> 20:09.334
That thing is so faulty,
I'd rather just get it replaced.

20:10.294 --> 20:11.879
You're leaving?

20:11.962 --> 20:14.047
Yeah, bud, but I'll be right back.

20:14.131 --> 20:16.091
(QUIETLY) Okay.

20:18.802 --> 20:20.095
I can go.

20:25.142 --> 20:27.728
-It's totally fine.
-Uh, are you sure?

20:27.811 --> 20:29.813
Yeah. Um...

20:31.565 --> 20:35.110
Absolutely. You... You stay here.

20:35.194 --> 20:37.487
I... I won't be gone very long.

20:37.571 --> 20:40.032
It's only just...
You know, I'll be about an hour.

20:40.115 --> 20:42.409
Okay.

20:42.492 --> 20:45.579
Okay, the disarm code's Oz's birthday.

20:47.706 --> 20:49.416
If it looks like there's been a break-in,
don't go inside.

20:49.499 --> 20:51.293
Don't go inside. Okay.

20:54.838 --> 20:56.840
I've got this. Okay?

20:58.926 --> 21:00.928
(ALARM WAILING)

21:22.950 --> 21:24.952
(ALARM CONTINUES WAILING)

21:38.841 --> 21:40.843
(ALARM STOPS)

21:53.355 --> 21:55.357
(SOFT METALLIC SQUEAKING IN DISTANCE)

22:05.117 --> 22:08.829
(SOFT METALLIC SQUEAKING CONTINUES)

22:12.541 --> 22:14.710
(FLIPS SWITCH)

22:14.793 --> 22:17.838
(FLIPPING SWITCH)

22:28.098 --> 22:30.100
(CLATTERING)

22:31.351 --> 22:32.561
(EXHALES)

22:32.644 --> 22:34.897
(PANTING, TREMBLING)

22:39.026 --> 22:41.236
(CONTINUES PANTING)

22:45.407 --> 22:47.367
(SCREAMING)

23:01.715 --> 23:03.592
(SHAKING DOOR)

23:05.928 --> 23:07.804
(TEAKETTLE WHISTLING)

23:15.604 --> 23:17.314
(WHISTLING STOPS)

23:19.399 --> 23:21.068
(DOOR OPENS)

23:21.151 --> 23:24.238
Hey, guess who happened to be
in the neighborhood.

23:24.321 --> 23:26.406
Ally, how are you?

23:33.121 --> 23:34.331
Tea?

23:34.957 --> 23:37.251
Sure. Just plain.

23:41.672 --> 23:43.966
Would you like a cup?

23:44.049 --> 23:48.762
Uh, no. I've got to pick some herbs
from the backyard for the restaurant.

23:48.846 --> 23:52.266
But, um, you guys can talk.

23:57.813 --> 23:59.857
Not very subtle, but...

23:59.940 --> 24:01.692
I guess she meant well.

24:01.775 --> 24:04.319
(CONSTRUCTION NOISE IN DISTANCE)

24:04.403 --> 24:06.154
(CUPS CLACK)

24:08.991 --> 24:12.703
Did she tell you I'm coming unglued?

24:12.786 --> 24:15.706
I was the one who reached out
when you missed your appointments.

24:17.416 --> 24:18.584
Thanks.

24:18.667 --> 24:20.836
Ivy told me about what happened.

24:26.133 --> 24:28.135
About the murder
in the restaurant last week.

24:29.928 --> 24:32.222
(BREATHES DEEPLY)

24:37.269 --> 24:40.439
Did she tell you
I was the one who killed him?

24:44.026 --> 24:46.612
<i>Roger was still alive</i>

24:46.695 --> 24:49.114
<i>when I found him.</i>

24:49.198 --> 24:52.117
<i>I tried to help him, but...</i>

24:52.201 --> 24:53.660
(SCREAMS)

24:57.372 --> 24:59.374
Ally, you didn't kill him.

24:59.458 --> 25:02.127
-You tried to save his life.
-(SNIFFLES)

25:02.211 --> 25:04.922
It's the truth,
and the police certainly know that.

25:05.005 --> 25:07.466
(LAUGH WRYLY)

25:07.549 --> 25:09.551
(WHISPERS) The police.

25:11.345 --> 25:15.182
They just wanted me
to pin it on the usual suspects.

25:15.265 --> 25:17.809
The busboy, what is his name again?

25:17.893 --> 25:19.978
The one who had the argument?

25:20.062 --> 25:22.814
It was Pedro Morales. (SNIFFLES)

25:22.898 --> 25:25.400
Is there anything else
you want to tell me about him?

25:25.484 --> 25:27.444
He's not the killer.

25:27.528 --> 25:30.948
Mmm. Well, according to your wife,

25:31.031 --> 25:34.618
Mr. Morales pulled a knife on the victim
hours before he was murdered.

25:34.701 --> 25:36.119
(EXHALES)

25:36.203 --> 25:39.289
That is because Roger
threatened him first.

25:39.373 --> 25:41.041
You said that he wanted him fired.

25:41.124 --> 25:43.085
So far we don't have any direct evidence,

25:43.168 --> 25:45.504
but we do have motive and we have access.

25:45.587 --> 25:47.422
I've known Pedro since
we opened the restaurant.

25:47.506 --> 25:49.591
He didn't do this.

25:50.634 --> 25:54.513
What exactly is
Mr. Morales' immigration status?

25:54.596 --> 25:56.515
He's American.

25:58.141 --> 25:59.852
VINCENT: <i>Ally,</i>

25:59.935 --> 26:02.479
let's talk about
how you feel in the present.

26:07.568 --> 26:10.988
I... I feel like I've been vindicated.

26:13.991 --> 26:17.744
My phobias were a perfect reaction

26:17.828 --> 26:21.206
to what I instinctively knew was true.

26:21.290 --> 26:24.585
My entire being was telling me this.

26:26.211 --> 26:29.047
The world is fucked up.

26:29.131 --> 26:32.134
And the election made it worse.

26:32.217 --> 26:36.388
I'm gonna do whatever it takes
to keep my family safe.

26:37.222 --> 26:39.474
HARRISON: I know exactly what you need.

26:39.558 --> 26:42.102
MEADOW: He's been buying guns
since Obama got elected.

26:42.186 --> 26:43.520
HARRISON: Yeah. It was a matter of time

26:43.604 --> 26:45.898
before he came after
our Second Amendment rights, so...

26:45.981 --> 26:49.610
I got one, and then it was
like potato chips, you know?

26:49.693 --> 26:50.694
I had to have another.

26:50.777 --> 26:52.738
I find it very phallic.

26:58.243 --> 27:00.078
You think I need a gun?

27:00.162 --> 27:02.664
It's the only thing
that's gonna make you feel safe again.

27:03.582 --> 27:04.625
What about this?

27:06.168 --> 27:09.546
You can stop the zombie apocalypse
with an AR-15 and a full magazine.

27:09.630 --> 27:11.173
(EXHALES) Uh...

27:11.256 --> 27:13.967
I don't think I could handle
something that big.

27:14.051 --> 27:15.385
Well, I've heard that before.

27:15.469 --> 27:16.512
(CHUCKLES)

27:16.595 --> 27:17.888
Here.

27:19.139 --> 27:22.559
You can have any one of these,

27:22.643 --> 27:24.478
except that one.

27:24.561 --> 27:27.814
Oh. That's the pistol Nicole used
in <i>Cold Mountain.</i>

27:32.611 --> 27:34.446
(SOFTLY) Ally.

27:34.530 --> 27:36.823
Ally, this is not like you.

27:36.907 --> 27:39.368
I seriously think you sh...

27:39.451 --> 27:40.702
Ally...

27:42.037 --> 27:43.497
I seriously think you should reconsider.

27:43.580 --> 27:45.707
Are you talking as my therapist,

27:45.791 --> 27:47.626
-or as a knee-jerk liberal?
-(SIGHS)

27:47.709 --> 27:53.173
Because that was my first reaction, also,
until I started to reason it out.

27:55.008 --> 27:56.552
Okay.

27:56.635 --> 27:59.429
Then this is definitely something
you want to tell your wife about.

27:59.513 --> 28:01.640
Absolutely not.

28:01.723 --> 28:04.017
And you're not gonna tell her, either.

28:04.101 --> 28:06.687
It's doctor-patient confidentiality.

28:09.231 --> 28:11.149
(SOFTLY) Right.

28:17.072 --> 28:18.532
Call me.

28:21.702 --> 28:23.287
(DOOR OPENS)

28:23.370 --> 28:24.663
(DOOR CLOSES)

28:27.124 --> 28:28.876
So, what's the verdict?

28:29.960 --> 28:31.461
Well, considering what she went through,

28:31.545 --> 28:35.424
I think fortifying the house
is in the realm of a normal reaction.

28:35.507 --> 28:37.426
It's proactive.

28:37.509 --> 28:39.678
Makes her feel like she's more in control.

28:39.761 --> 28:42.181
So, nothing to worry about?

28:43.265 --> 28:47.936
Well, I do worry that she's exhibiting
early signs of agoraphobia.

28:48.020 --> 28:49.897
I'd keep an eye on her.

28:49.980 --> 28:51.565
I... I can't. Um... (CHUCKLES)

28:51.648 --> 28:53.358
I mean, one of us has to work.

28:54.401 --> 28:56.695
But I, um...
I just hired a full-time nanny,

28:56.778 --> 28:59.281
so maybe she can help, um...

29:02.743 --> 29:06.288
Is there anything else
you need to tell me?

29:09.166 --> 29:11.001
No, nothing yet.

29:12.336 --> 29:14.588
That's not completely reassuring.

29:15.964 --> 29:18.800
It's the best I can do for now.

29:20.302 --> 29:21.553
Thank you.

29:24.848 --> 29:26.266
(CAR DOOR OPENS)

29:27.518 --> 29:28.602
(DOOR CLOSES)

29:28.685 --> 29:30.562
(ENGINE STARTS)

29:39.321 --> 29:41.365
I can't believe you did that.

29:41.448 --> 29:43.492
I'm worried about you.

29:43.575 --> 29:46.495
(QUIETLY) Yeah. You should be.

29:52.334 --> 29:54.336
-(CAR DOOR CLOSES)
-(ENGINE STARTS)

29:54.419 --> 29:57.673
(DRILL WHIRRING)

30:06.098 --> 30:08.851
(RHYTHMIC KNOCKING)

30:22.823 --> 30:25.033
(KNOCKING)

30:31.039 --> 30:33.792
KAI: Hello, ma'am. Miss.

30:33.876 --> 30:36.712
I never know what's right.
Everything seems to offend nowadays.

30:38.505 --> 30:41.800
I recognize you from television. Yeah.

30:42.926 --> 30:46.138
You're that asshole who threw
a latte on my wife and me.

30:46.221 --> 30:47.848
Is that right?

30:47.931 --> 30:49.600
Was that you?

30:49.683 --> 30:51.059
I'm so sorry.

30:51.143 --> 30:53.437
Okay? I... I'm Mr. Clumsy,
you know, just...

30:53.520 --> 30:55.105
Mr. Butterfingers.

30:55.189 --> 30:56.815
I don't think it was an accident.

30:57.941 --> 30:59.860
I'm sure you've made
a mistake or two in your life

30:59.943 --> 31:01.528
you'd want to be forgiven for.

31:03.572 --> 31:05.073
What do you want?

31:05.157 --> 31:07.075
I'm running for city council.

31:07.159 --> 31:10.412
My hope is that I can get elected
and be known and remembered

31:10.495 --> 31:12.372
as the man who made a real
difference in this town,

31:12.456 --> 31:15.042
rather than the one who was
savagely beaten and humiliated.

31:15.125 --> 31:17.794
Or who accidentally
spilled my latte on you.

31:17.878 --> 31:20.464
You see... You need to give
a humiliated man

31:20.547 --> 31:23.091
some way to redeem himself
in his own eyes,

31:23.175 --> 31:25.928
or else he's at risk
to be drawn into darkness.

31:26.011 --> 31:28.805
Like Germany after World War I.

31:28.889 --> 31:32.142
May I come in and speak to you
about some of my ideas?

31:33.352 --> 31:35.729
No. No, you cannot.

31:35.812 --> 31:38.982
When was the last time
you felt really safe?

31:39.066 --> 31:44.238
Like, can you remember
when you weren't scared all the time?

31:44.321 --> 31:46.281
I'm sorry, um...

31:46.365 --> 31:48.492
What does that have to do
with you running for city council?

31:48.575 --> 31:52.746
Did you know that you are 40% more likely
to be the victim of a violent crime

31:52.829 --> 31:54.706
committed at the hands
of an illegal immigrant,

31:54.790 --> 31:58.418
and that the murder and rape rates
are the highest they've ever been?

31:58.502 --> 32:01.839
That... That's not true.
Those numbers don't seem right to me.

32:01.922 --> 32:04.132
(LAUGHS) Where are you
getting your information from?

32:05.175 --> 32:06.635
Facebook.

32:06.718 --> 32:07.970
Facebook.

32:09.763 --> 32:12.850
Okay, well, you might want
to recheck the veracity.

32:12.933 --> 32:15.185
There are no political parties
anymore, ma'am.

32:15.269 --> 32:17.521
It's just... Miss...
It's just them and you

32:17.604 --> 32:20.941
and the people like me
who are willing to stand between you.

32:21.024 --> 32:25.696
I am interested in reaching out to people,
making contact with other human beings,

32:25.779 --> 32:28.323
building bridges, not walls.

32:31.660 --> 32:33.453
What's that behind your back?

32:35.622 --> 32:37.207
This door is new.

32:39.459 --> 32:40.669
Strong.

32:40.752 --> 32:43.297
Why would you need
a strong door like this?

32:43.380 --> 32:45.174
Bars in the windows?

32:46.425 --> 32:49.511
Why would you need a knife
to answer the door?

32:49.595 --> 32:54.016
Are you gonna melt all this metal down
and build a bridge?

32:56.059 --> 32:58.395
I'm gonna need you to leave now.

32:58.478 --> 33:00.606
Mmm. It's so hot out here. Can I come in

33:00.689 --> 33:02.357
-for a glass of water? Please?
-No.

33:02.441 --> 33:03.734
No, you cannot.

33:03.817 --> 33:06.945
Can I use your phone?
My car broke down. Pretty please?

33:07.029 --> 33:09.281
I'm gonna need you to get off my property.

33:09.364 --> 33:11.867
Can I use your restroom?
Can't you see I'm an injured man?

33:11.950 --> 33:13.202
Aren't a vulnerable class now?

33:13.285 --> 33:15.037
I am going to call the police!

33:15.120 --> 33:20.125
It's so easy
until it's you they're coming for.

33:23.879 --> 33:26.632
Cops came to my house,
asked me a bunch of questions

33:26.715 --> 33:28.509
like I was a suspect.

33:28.592 --> 33:30.302
Scared the shit out of my daughter.

33:30.385 --> 33:33.597
Asked to see my papers.
I was born in San Diego.

33:33.680 --> 33:37.017
Okay, all right. Take it easy.

33:37.100 --> 33:39.728
I had to take out
a second mortgage on my house

33:39.811 --> 33:41.313
to place this order.

33:42.439 --> 33:44.942
Had to toss everything
that was here when...

33:45.025 --> 33:46.860
(PANTING)

33:54.493 --> 33:56.870
You know me, Ivy.

33:56.954 --> 33:58.622
You know I didn't do this, right?

33:58.705 --> 33:59.790
(EXHALES)

33:59.873 --> 34:01.834
Pedro, you're a good man.

34:01.917 --> 34:04.795
Everybody who works here is like family.

34:06.255 --> 34:08.549
It's scary to be brown these days.

34:12.177 --> 34:14.513
Mama's not gonna put me in bed, is she?

34:14.596 --> 34:17.474
I told her I'd do it.
She's checking the alarms.

34:17.558 --> 34:20.602
You don't need me to tuck you in
or any lame shit like that, do you?

34:20.686 --> 34:21.812
No.

34:21.895 --> 34:24.147
Cool. Good night.

34:25.482 --> 34:26.608
Hey.

34:27.985 --> 34:30.320
Maybe we should do the pinky thing again.

34:30.404 --> 34:32.030
Why?

34:32.114 --> 34:35.534
I'm worried about those things
coming back.

34:35.617 --> 34:38.161
In my dreams, I mean.

34:38.245 --> 34:41.623
I don't even know if I'm awake
or if I'm asleep.

34:41.707 --> 34:44.501
Well, if you're not sure, just ask.

35:04.855 --> 35:06.732
-Oh, my God.
-Jesus.

35:06.815 --> 35:08.817
-(SIGHS)
-You seem even more uptight than usual.

35:11.028 --> 35:12.154
(GROANS)

35:17.284 --> 35:19.494
I'm supposed to take these. (SNIFFLES)

35:20.787 --> 35:23.624
Promised Ivy I would, but I don't want to.

35:26.293 --> 35:28.045
Make me feel foggy.

35:29.546 --> 35:33.675
-There are other ways to unwind.
-What, like meditation?

35:33.759 --> 35:35.344
(SCOFFS)

35:35.427 --> 35:37.054
I've tried it.

35:37.137 --> 35:41.975
Well, I was thinking more like red wine
and bath salts.

35:45.854 --> 35:47.814
(KNOB CREAKS)

36:12.089 --> 36:14.424
You don't have to do that.

36:14.508 --> 36:16.426
It's fine.

36:16.510 --> 36:18.178
(SIGHS)

36:18.262 --> 36:20.055
Steamy.

36:31.984 --> 36:34.570
-I can take it from here.
-Okay.

36:34.653 --> 36:37.072
Well, it's perfect.

36:37.155 --> 36:39.283
I'll go check on Oz.

36:44.162 --> 36:45.497
(DOOR CLOSES)

36:54.673 --> 36:56.216
(DISTORTED, ECHOING CLACK)

36:56.300 --> 36:58.760
(EXHALES SLOWLY)

37:12.441 --> 37:15.235
(BREATHES DEEPLY)

37:22.075 --> 37:25.370
See? It's perfect, right?

37:27.080 --> 37:30.083
Winter. (CHUCKLES SOFTLY)

37:30.167 --> 37:32.127
Just lean forward a little.

37:32.211 --> 37:34.796
(LAUGHS SOFTLY)

37:34.880 --> 37:36.798
What if Ozzie needs something?

37:36.882 --> 37:38.717
He's sound asleep. We'll hear him.

37:39.259 --> 37:42.137
Come on. Let's get you relaxed.

37:51.688 --> 37:53.315
How does that feel?

37:55.817 --> 37:57.402
Amazing.

37:57.486 --> 37:59.154
Good.

37:59.238 --> 38:01.740
Just release that tension.

38:01.823 --> 38:04.076
Just let it all go.

38:22.344 --> 38:23.929
(SOFT SPLASH)

38:27.266 --> 38:28.767
Don't stress.

38:28.851 --> 38:30.936
I won't tell your wife
you didn't take your meds.

38:32.312 --> 38:33.689
This is between us.

38:37.442 --> 38:39.486
(ALARM BLARING)

38:39.570 --> 38:41.405
Oh, shit. Oh, shit.

38:41.488 --> 38:43.490
(ALARM STOPS)

38:44.575 --> 38:45.617
(GASPS)

38:48.662 --> 38:50.122
Am I asleep?

38:50.205 --> 38:52.374
Or are you real?

38:52.457 --> 38:54.251
You're asleep.

39:13.520 --> 39:15.480
-Did you check on Oz? Is he okay?
-He's passed out.

39:15.564 --> 39:17.274
Did you see?
The power's out on the whole block.

39:17.357 --> 39:19.943
Yes. Help me set up some candles.
I have no idea how many we have,

39:20.027 --> 39:22.112
but maybe we can put two in each room.

39:22.196 --> 39:25.032
-(BANGING ON DOOR)
-HARRISON: Lesbians!

39:25.115 --> 39:26.658
We're under attack.

39:26.742 --> 39:28.660
-What?
-The blackout. It's terrorism.

39:28.744 --> 39:30.829
I just heard it on the radio.
Eight states just went dark,

39:30.913 --> 39:33.123
all at the same time.
That doesn't just happen.

39:33.207 --> 39:35.125
Buddy of mine used to work
at the power company.

39:35.209 --> 39:38.295
There's a whole network of safeguards
in place, backup systems.

39:38.378 --> 39:40.797
Something this big takes planning,
it takes organization.

39:40.881 --> 39:42.674
It could have been the Russians,
could have been the Somalis,

39:42.758 --> 39:44.301
could be those crazy freaks
in North Korea.

39:44.384 --> 39:46.303
Holy shit. What should we do?

39:46.386 --> 39:47.679
Make sure you keep your doors locked.

39:47.763 --> 39:50.307
People are gonna panic.
Here, take these candles.

39:50.390 --> 39:52.267
Organic beeswax from my honeybees.

39:52.351 --> 39:53.393
They'll last you a couple of days,

39:53.477 --> 39:56.021
at least until the rioters
have come and gone.

39:56.104 --> 39:57.648
Stay inside.

39:57.731 --> 39:59.066
Please don't go!

40:00.817 --> 40:01.944
Shit.

40:03.237 --> 40:05.614
(PANTS, STAMMERS)

40:09.576 --> 40:12.454
Winter, what are you doing?

40:12.538 --> 40:14.873
What are you doing?

40:14.957 --> 40:16.500
He said people are gonna attack.
I'm not gonna wait

40:16.583 --> 40:18.293
for some asshole to smash my windows
and take my shit.

40:18.377 --> 40:19.837
You heard what he said.

40:19.920 --> 40:21.547
You cannot go out there. It is not safe.

40:21.630 --> 40:24.800
I've got to get home. My laptop's there,
my ceramics, my entire life.

40:24.883 --> 40:27.636
You can replace all of that.
You have to stay here.

40:27.719 --> 40:29.513
We are protected here. Please.

40:29.596 --> 40:31.807
Please. Oz needs you, I need you.

40:31.890 --> 40:33.559
It's not always about you.

40:33.642 --> 40:36.854
Winter, please don't go.

40:36.937 --> 40:39.898
-Please don't!
-(DOOR CLOSES)

40:44.820 --> 40:47.239
(BREATH TREMBLING)

40:51.618 --> 40:53.579
Ivy, Ivy, Ivy.

40:53.662 --> 40:56.164
Ivy, Ivy, Ivy...

40:56.248 --> 40:59.543
-(CELL PHONE BUZZING)
-(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

40:59.626 --> 41:01.920
Hey, babe. Is the power out there, too?

41:02.004 --> 41:04.381
Yes. Yes. Oh, my God, Ivy.

41:04.464 --> 41:07.050
What if it's the Russians or... Or ISIS?

41:07.134 --> 41:09.386
Okay, calm down. You're...

41:09.469 --> 41:11.388
You got to relax, okay?
You're freaking out.

41:11.471 --> 41:13.807
(CRYING) I can't calm down.
We are by ourselves.

41:14.850 --> 41:17.728
We're by ourselves,
and my battery is gonna die.

41:17.811 --> 41:19.146
When are you coming home?

41:19.229 --> 41:21.857
<i>Yeah, I... I don't know, because I've got</i>
<i>to get a backup generator</i> going,

41:21.940 --> 41:24.526
<i>or we'll lose everything</i>
<i>we've got in cold storage, okay? And...</i>

41:24.610 --> 41:26.361
I am really feeling paralyzed here.

41:26.445 --> 41:28.238
Please. I need you.

41:28.322 --> 41:30.240
(RAPID BEEPING OVER PHONE)

41:30.324 --> 41:32.409
Ivy? Hello?

41:32.492 --> 41:33.911
Shit!

41:36.413 --> 41:37.497
Was that mean?

41:37.581 --> 41:39.583
-Did I sound awful?
-PEDRO: No.

41:39.666 --> 41:41.418
I talk to my wife like that.

41:45.923 --> 41:47.799
Her phone just died.

41:47.883 --> 41:52.012
Um, could you do me a favor and, um,

41:52.095 --> 41:54.014
bring this charger over to her?

41:55.140 --> 41:58.894
You know what? Actually, would you bring
all this stuff to her?

41:58.977 --> 42:01.271
I'll get some water.

42:01.355 --> 42:03.232
(LOCK CLACKS)

42:03.315 --> 42:06.485
(PANTING, TREMBLING)

42:11.031 --> 42:12.699
(CRYING) Come on...

42:12.783 --> 42:14.910
(DOOR CREAKING)

42:20.999 --> 42:23.001
(BREATHING DEEPLY)

42:40.435 --> 42:42.771
